Package <Unnamed>

Interface Summary
Portalable An interface that determines that whether an object can have a portal placed on it.
 

Class Summary
EnrichmentCenter  
Game An abstract Game class which can be built into Pong.

The default controls are for "Player 1" to move left and right with the 'Z' and 'X' keys, and "Playr 2" to move left and right with the 'N' and 'M' keys.

Before the Game begins, the setup method is executed.
GameObject An abstract class for an object which can be added to an instance of Game

The act method can be implemented to provide a behavior for the object, and will be called every millisecond automatically by a Game it has been added to.
GreenWall This wall will end the level.
HardWall A HardWall is a wall that may not have a Portal placed on it.
LevelThree Another level for PortalGame, created by overriding the getWalls(), getPotatoes(), and main(String[]) methods.
LevelTwo The most advanced PortalGame level.
MusicPlayer MusicPlayer lets you play an MP3 file in the background while using your application.
It extends Thread to do this.
Some methods will throw IllegalStateExceptions and other errors if the files are not correct.
Player Player.java
The Player class maintains the player's movement and her location and size.
Portal A Portal is a GameObject which teleports a user from one Portal to another.
In PortalGame (and subclasses), when the Player collides with a Portal, they exit the other.
PortalGame The driver for Portal.
PortalTrail  
Potato A Potato is a scoring object which determines the percentage of completion.
RedWall A RedWall is a Wall that cannot be Portalled and will reset the player.
Wall A wall that can be Portalled.
